  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "First, Ovsyannikova and colleagues had raters review descriptions of personal emotional experiences and a compassionate response to these scenarios by either AI (GPT-4), non-expert humans, or hotline crisis responders, showing that AI was rated as more compassionate and was preferred compared to even expert humans.",
    "Second, Yin and colleagues had humans share a recent \"complex situation\" in real-time interaction with either another human or GPT-4, showing again that participants reported feeling more heard when engaging with the AI.",
    "These studies suggest that in short conversations, GPT-4 is rated as better at emotional support than humans.",
    "AI could be better for a variety of reasons, and the goal of the current paper is to begin to unpack them.",
    "One question is to what extent differences in performance are driven by skill or effort."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}